Slice open the @97% pork sausages{500%g} and remove the meat (discard the skin). Break
into roughly 2cm pieces. (Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!)
Put a small splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the
sausage meat and fry for ~{10-12%minutes}, turning occasionally. You want it to
brown, but nice and gently. Once cooked, transfer to a plate (no need to wash
the pan).

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the
broccoli. Halve, peel and slice the @echalion shallot{2} into thin half moons.
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut the
@chestnut mushrooms{1} into thin slices. Cut the @broccoli{1} into florets
(small trees!). Finely chop the @chives{1}.

Pop the @cardamom pods{4} in another large saucepan with the @water for the rice{600%ml}.
Add a pinch of @salt{} and the @basmati rice{300%g} and bring to a boil. Pop on
a #lid{}, reduce the heat to low and cook for ~{10%minutes}. After 10 mins,
remove the pan from the heat. Leave the lid on and set aside for a further
~{10%minutes}. The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, add the mushrooms to the (now empty) frying pan. Cook for
~{5%minutes} then add the shallot. Cook until the shallot is soft and caramelised,
another ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> TIP: If the kids don't like mushrooms, fry them in another pan and serve them
> separately for those who do.

Add the @water{150%ml} and the @chicken stock pot{1}. Stir to dissolve.

Return the sausage pieces to the pan and add the @peas{200%g}. Lower the heat
to medium. Simmer for ~{5%minutes} then stir in the @creme fraiche{1}. Bring the
stew back to a boil, then remove from the heat. Stir in the chives, taste and
add @salt{} and @black pepper{} if you feel it needs it.

Add the broccoli to your pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{4%minutes} then drain
in a #colander{}. Remove the cardamom pods from your rice and fluff it up with a
#fork{}. Serve some rice with a helping of creamy sausage stew on top and the
broccoli alongside. Enjoy!